17231,22.616585 L7.00408269,14.8432273 L0.212864685,10.0456121 C-0.0140805533,9.88528803 -0.0680876559,9.57134421 0.0922364448,9.34439897 C0.186520784,9.21093568 0.339749724,9.1315756 0.503157148,9.1315756 L8.910885,9.1315756 L11.5230185,1.34326985 C11.6113744,1.0798288 11.8965622,0.937894292 12.1600033,1.02625024 C12.3095218,1.07639751 12.4268756,1.19375135 12.4770229,1.34326985 Z"></path></g></svg></span></span></div><span class="Text Text__body3"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2319534229">Edited <!-- -->March 7, 2021</a></span></section><section class="ReviewText"><section class="ReviewText__content"><div class="TruncatedText"><div class="TruncatedText__text TruncatedText__text--5" data-testid="contentContainer"><div><span class="Formatted">A continuation of the easy bestselling, pythonesc blasphemous highway to hell that is often just driven to provoke, but masterfully executed in Moore´s by far best book.<br /><br />No spoiler warning, but a sacrilege notification, because this book and the review might be nothing for faithful people.<br /><br />I don´t know who of you knows the story, just let me spoiler it and tell you that it doesn´t end great, ok? It´s just for protection, I don´t want you to be sad if the sympathetic main character has to get through some terrible PTSD moments. But at least Moore gave him a good friend to record a Big History, biographical analysis of good, old JC.<br /><br />Cause I´ve never read any holy texts, except you define trying to invoke succubi, yes, you´ve heard right, plural, I am greedy, I maybe don´t get all the innuendos and side blows Moore puts in this tour de force of sarcastic faith criticism. But I will just assume that I didn´t miss much. <br /><br />It´s kind of strange that, in the 21st century, the old Christian, and especially Catholic church, are the only ones who can be made fun of, because taboos and false tolerance of world improvers or the danger of death in religious states is circulating when doing it with other faiths. Of course, backlashes and strengthening extremism is a thing with Christian religions too, but the scales, dangers, and dimension are completely different ones. <br /><br />In both cases, such literature isn´t meant to hurt and insult religious people, it´s their fault if they read obviously satirical texts and can´t handle it, the real important purpose instead is to open the minds of still not brainwashed people, criticize the idea of monotheism, polytheism, any religion, and use the mightiest, the funny, sword pen to promote tolerance and reduce the self righteousness megalomania attitude that sadly often comes through the backdoor. Well meant attitudes and people trying to live good lives are instrumentalized by demagogic, power hungry master manipulators without having a chance. <br /><br />That´s why the freedom of any kind of satire about each topic thinkable is one of the most profound signs of enlightened, Western democracies, I once find nothing to complain about, and why past, current, and coming attempts of conservative, right wing fanatics to reintroduce any kind of private church state faith indoctrination complex in Europe or North America have to be fought with the true and good enthusiasm of holy warriors.<br /><br />I like Neal Stephenson, he lets his characters say things I´ll mix together to one hybrid quote:<br />“This Snow Crash thing--is it a virus, a drug, or a religion?”<br /> „What's the difference, we are all susceptible to the pull of viral ideas. Like mass hysteria. Or a tune that gets into your head that you keep humming all day until you spread it to someone else. Jokes. Urban legends. Crackpot religions. No matter how smart we get, there is always this deep irrational part that makes us potential hosts for parasitic, self-replicating information.“<br /><br />Tropes show how literature is conceptualized and created and which mixture of elements makes works and genres unique: <br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LambTheGospelAccordingToBiff">https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.ph...</a></span></div></div></div></section></section><section class="ReviewCard__tags"><ul class="CollapsableList"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/78485297?shelf=moore-christopher" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem">moore-christopher</span></a></ul></section><footer class="SocialFooter"><div data-testid="stats" class="SocialFooter__statsContainer"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small Button--subdued"><span class="Button__labelItem">187 likes</span></button></div><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small Button--subdued"><span class="Button__labelItem">4 comments</span></button></div></div><div data-testid="actions"><div class="SocialFooter__action"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem"><i class="Icon LikeIcon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M14.4813282,6.41129383 L14.586127,6.97676447 C14.5964421,7.03541935 14.6071117,7.09675198 14.6181364,7.1607667 L14.8551301,8.60363442 L17.440983,8.60363442 C18.1623576,8.60363442 18.8218187,9.01120377 19.1444272,9.65642083 L19.1708204,9.70920723 C19.4523479,10.2722622 19.4523479,10.9350066 19.1708204,11.4980616 L19.118034,11.6036344 L19.1708204,11.7092072 C19.4523479,12.2722622 19.4523479,12.9350066 19.1708204,13.4980616 L19.118034,13.6036344 L19.1708204,13.7092072 C19.4523479,14.2722622 19.4523479,14.9350066 19.1708204,15.4980616 L19,15.8397024 L19,16.1036344 C19,16.7361314 18.6701344,17.3185188 18.1373501,17.6453922 L17.9472136,17.7480616 C17.4795438,17.9818965 16.9638538,18.1036344 16.440983,18.1036344 L9.66834148,18.1034086 C9.31027068,18.6437214 8.696742,19 8,19 L6,19 C4.8954305,19 4,18.1045695 4,17 L4,12 C4,10.8954305 4.8954